{"cursor":"12175","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"'Site-directed mutagenesis' is a molecular biology method that is used to make\nspecific and intentional changes to the DNA sequence of a gene and any gene\nproducts. Also called site-specific mutagenesis or oligonucleotide-directed\nmutagenesis, it is used for investigating the structure and biological activity\nof DNA, RNA, and protein molecules, and for protein engineering. With decreasing\ncosts of oligonucleotide synthesis, artificial gene synthesis is now\noccasionally used as an alternative to site-directed mutagenesis.\n","linknr":276,"url":"Site-directed_mutagenesis","recorded":1362371320,"links":31,"instances":["molecular_biology","genetics","genetics","genetics","gene","dna","chemist"],"pdf":["http://www.jbc.org/content/253/18/6551.full.pdf"],"categories":["Molecular genetics","Mutagenesis","Protein engineering"],"headings":["History","Basic mechanism","Approaches in site-directed mutagenesis","Applications","See also","References","External links"],"image":["//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/vector/images/search-ltr.png?303-4","//bits.wikimedia.org/images/wikimedia-button.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf10/skins/common/images/poweredby_mediawiki_88x31.png"],"tags":[["transition","genetics"],["michael_smith","chemist"],["deletion","genetics"],["insertion","genetics"],["dut","gene"],["primer","molecular_biology"],["nick","dna"]],"members":["primer","insertion","transition","deletion","dut","nick","michael_smith"],"related":["Molecular_biology","DNA_sequence","Gene","Gene_product","DNA","RNA","Protein","Protein_engineering","Oligonucleotide_synthesis","Artificial_gene_synthesis","Point_mutations","Aminopurine","Methylnitronitrosoguanidine","Bisulfite","Charles_Weissmann","Transition_(genetics)","Clyde_Hutchison","Phi_X_174","Restriction_nuclease","Michael_Smith_(chemist)","Oligonucleotide","Nobel_Prize_in_Chemistry","Kary_B._Mullis","Polymerase_chain_reaction","Oligonucl